.\" Man page for sc - Scientific Calculator
.\" Process with: groff -man -Tascii sc.1
.TH SC 1 "December 2024" "sc 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sc \- arbitrary precision scientific calculator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sc
[\fIexpression\fR]
.br
echo \fIexpression\fR |
.B sc
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sc
is an interactive arbitrary precision scientific calculator supporting
complex numbers, matrices, and a wide range of mathematical functions.
It uses 128-bit quad precision floating point internally for high accuracy.
.PP
When run without arguments,
.B sc
enters interactive mode with a
.B >>>
prompt (like bc). When given an expression as an argument or via stdin,
it evaluates and prints the result.
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Arbitrary Precision
128-bit quad precision (approximately 34 significant digits)
.TP
.B Complex Numbers
Full support for complex arithmetic using
.I i
as the imaginary unit
.TP
.B Matrices
Create, manipulate, and perform linear algebra operations on matrices
.TP
.B Scientific Functions
Trigonometric, hyperbolic, exponential, logarithmic, and special functions
.TP
.B Multiple Number Formats
Decimal, hexadecimal (0x), binary (0b), octal (0o), and Roman numerals
.SH OPERATORS
.TP
.B + \- * /
Basic arithmetic (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division)
.TP
.B ^
Exponentiation (right associative: 2^3^2 = 2^9 = 512)
.TP
.B %
Modulo
.TP
.B !
Factorial (postfix)
.TP
.B ( )
Grouping
.SH FUNCTIONS
.SS Trigonometric (radians)
.B sin cos tan asin acos atan atan2
.SS Hyperbolic
.B sinh cosh tanh asinh acosh atanh
.SS Exponential and Logarithmic
.B exp
\- exponential (e^x)
.br
.B log ln
\- natural logarithm
.br
.B log10
\- base-10 logarithm
.br
.B log2
\- base-2 logarithm
.SS Power and Root
.B sqrt cbrt
\- square root, cube root
.br
.B pow(x,y)
\- x raised to power y
.SS Complex Number Functions
.B abs arg conj real imag
.br
.B phase polar rect
.SS Other Functions
.B floor ceil round trunc frac
.br
.B min max gcd lcm
.br
.B rand randn randi
\- random numbers
.SH CONSTANTS
.TP
.B pi
3.14159265358979323846...
.TP
.B e
2.71828182845904523536...
.TP
.B i
Imaginary unit (sqrt(-1))
.TP
.B Inf
Positive infinity
.TP
.B NaN
Not a number
.TP
.B ans
Result of previous calculation
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B help
Display help information
.TP
.B digits \fIN\fR
Set display precision to N significant figures (default 16, max 37)
.TP
.B round \fIMODE\fR
Set rounding mode: nearest, ceil, floor, trunc, away
.TP
.B vars
Show defined variables
.TP
.B clear
Clear all variables
.TP
.B test
Run built-in test suite
.TP
.B quit
Exit the calculator
.SH VARIABLES
Single-letter variables (a-z) can be assigned values:
.PP
.RS
>>> x = 5
.br
>>> y = x^2
.br
>>> y
.br
= 25
.RE
.SH MATRICES
Matrices are defined using square brackets:
.PP
.RS
>>> A = [1,2;3,4]
.br
>>> B = [5,6;7,8]
.br
>>> A * B
.RE
.PP
Matrix functions include:
.B inv transpose det trace eye zeros ones diag
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic arithmetic:
>>> 2 + 3 * 4
.br
= 14
.TP
Complex numbers:
>>> sqrt(\-1)
.br
= i
.br
>>> (1+2i) * (3\-4i)
.br
= 11+2i
.TP
Euler's identity:
>>> exp(i*pi) + 1
.br
= 0
.TP
Previous answer:
>>> 1/3
.br
= 0.3333333333333333
.br
>>> ans * 3
.br
= 1
.TP
Multiple expressions:
>>> 2+3; ans*2
.br
= 10
.TP
Hexadecimal input:
>>> 0xFF + 1
.br
= 256
.TP
Matrix operations:
>>> A = [1,2;3,4]
.br
>>> det(A)
.br
= \-2
.br
>>> inv(A)
.SH MODES
.TP
.B rpn
Reverse Polish Notation mode (HP calculator style)
.TP
.B tvm
Time Value of Money calculations
.TP
.B stat
Statistical calculations with data entry
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error in expression or calculation
.SH NOTES
.B log()
and
.B ln()
both compute the natural logarithm. Use
.B log10()
for base-10 logarithm.
.PP
Exponentiation is right-associative: 2^3^2 = 2^(3^2) = 512
.PP
The
.B ans
variable is updated after each expression, including those
separated by semicolons.
.SH IEEE 754 COMPLIANCE
.B sc
implements IEEE 754-2008 compliant arithmetic including proper handling of:
.IP \(bu 2
Infinity (+Inf, \-Inf)
.IP \(bu 2
Not-a-Number (NaN)
.IP \(bu 2
Signed zero (+0, \-0)
.IP \(bu 2
Special function domain errors
